---

!! Syntax

```
kanban
  columnId[Column Title]
    itemId[Item label]
    itemId[Item label]@{ assigned: 'user', ticket: REF-1, priority: 'High' }
```

* Each column is declared as `columnId[Title]`.
* Items are indented under their column.
* Metadata is appended with `@{ key: 'value', ... }` — supported keys: `assigned`, `ticket`, `priority`.

!! Tips

* Column and item IDs must be unique within the diagram and contain no spaces.
* Kanban is a ''read-only snapshot'' — it does not support drag-and-drop interaction.
* The number of columns is unlimited, but wide boards may overflow on small screens.

